SIMPLE: censer
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Censer
<hw>Cen"ser</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[For
<ets>incenser</ets>, fr. OF. <ets>encensier</ets>, F.
<ets>encensoir</ets>, fr. LL. <ets>incensarium</ets>,
<ets>incensorium</ets>, fr. L. <ets>incensum</ets> incense. See
<er>Incense</er>, and cf. <er>Incensory</er>.]</ety> <def>A vessel for
perfumes; esp. one in which incense is burned.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The ecclesiastical censer is usually cup-shaped, has a
cover pierced with holes, and is hung by chains. The censer bearer
swings it to quicken the combustion.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Her thoughts are like the fume of frankincense⟦br⟧
Which from a golden <qex>censer</qex> forth doth rise.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Censor</ent>⟦br⟧
